About Us – Vertical Petroleum Industries


























































 






About UsYou are here: Home / About Us





Vertical Petroleum Industries was founded by a real estate and oil investor who was tired of being offered overpriced projects from people who had little to no control over major development decisions. He assembled a team with a trusted operator and geologist to acquire and develop proven shallow vertical fields in northern Texas.
 
 

Dan Sauer, President of Vertical Petroleum Industries LLC
President and CEO of Vertical Petroleum Industries LLC in Ardmore, Oklahoma. Dan has been involved in Capital Funding for both oil and gas projects and for National and International Real Estate Projects for over 20 years. His experience includes 10 years as Director of Funding for projects totaling in excess of $60 million per year. In addition to Dan’s commercial real estate experience, Dan actively manages his personal portfolio of residential rental properties. Dan lives in the Plainview district of Ardmore, Oklahoma with Christie, his wife of 22 years, and their children.
 
 
 

 Newport Operating LLC
Newport Operating LLC was founded by an oil and gas investor in 2013 to maintain closer control over the development and day to day operations of his interests. Since that time, Newport has successfully operated numerous shallow wells in the area by building strong relationships with the community and local industry partners. Newport’s field operations supervisor began in the industry in 1995. Mr. Fort has drilled more than 200 successful shallow wells and oversees third party drilling contractors, geophysicists, engineers, and service companies.
 
 


LGT Corporation – Geology
LGT’s team consists of engineers, physicists, geophysicists, and geologist that have worked together over the last eight years to develop specialized software tools and analytical capability for the exploration, development, and evaluation of oil and gas prospects. LGT has pioneered the use of advanced geostatistics to integrate a wide range of independent datasets in order to maximize subsurface understanding and improve commercial success rates. Using conventional seismic and well log data, LGT supplements this data with isostatic gravity, magnetics, specialized radar, thermal imaging, radiometrics, geomorphology, formation mapping, and hyperspectral imaging. The combination of these independent datasets substantially reduces the risk of “false positives”, (dry holes) and improves the chances of commercial success.
 

Dr. Robert Miles, President of LGT Corporation
Dr. Rob Miles holds a PhD in Applied Physics from Caltech and a Bachelor of Science degree in Physics from the US Naval Academy. He served as a Nuclear Engineer in the Navy under Admiral Rickover and performed material characterization research at IBM’s Research Center in York Town Heights. He also worked at NASAs Jet Propulsion Labs on remote methods for material characterization. He worked at McKinsey and Company, consulting on risk analysis and risk management for several major companies in the energy industry.  At Koch Industries, Dr. Miles analyzed new technology developments in oil and gas. Before the start of LGT, he worked with Hunt Oil and Sevin Rosen Funds to evaluate oil and gas exploration technologies for investment and development.
 
 

Dr. Scott Douglas, Chief Technology Officer of LGT Corporation
Dr. Scott Douglas earned his B.S., M.S., and Ph.D. degrees in Electrical Engineering from Stanford.  He is a Full Professor of Electrical Engineering at Southern Methodist University and is a recognized world expert in signal processing techniques and methods.  He has published numerous book chapters and over 150 journal and conference papers on signal processing techniques, including several plenary and tutorial talks at international conferences and meetings. He has developed numerous innovative numerical methods and enhancements in various fields, including acoustics, image processing, and wireless systems.  He has worked extensively in various government projects, including sponsored work with the U.S. Army and ONR, along with collaborative efforts with several companies in the defense and information technology spaces.
 
 







